President Biden delivered a speech at the NJ Transit Meadowlands Maintenance Complex in Kearny, New Jersey, highlighting the importance of investing in infrastructure and early education. He praised Governor Murphy for his leadership in areas such as healthcare, education, and environmental protection. The President emphasized the need to rebuild America's infrastructure, which currently ranks 13th in the world, and discussed the significance of projects like the Portal Bridge, which is the busiest rail span in the Western Hemisphere. He also outlined his plans to create jobs, address climate change, and improve access to affordable childcare and preschool education. President Biden stressed the importance of investing in America's future and called on Congress to pass the infrastructure and Build Back Better bills.